LAST UPDATES

Reliable Knowledge about Reliable AI

New details on the new Konrad Zuse School of Excellence in Reliable AI (relAI) have been released. It will be jointly organized by TUM and LMU. Cooperation partners include the Fraunhofer Institutes for Cognitive Systems and for Applied and Integrated Security and the Helmholtz Zentrum München, as well as AI centers from all over the world, such as at the universities of Stanford and Princeton, New York University, and EPFL and commercial enterprises such as Google, Siemens and Munich Re.

Read the full press release here

Content Moderation: Extreme Speech and the (In)Significance of Artificial Intelligence

This new discussion paper at Harvard Kennedy School's Shorenstein Center on Media, Politics and Public Policy presents new empirical evidence on machine learning methods for content moderation. The paper is co-authored by LMU researchers Prof. Dr. Sahana Udupa, Antonis Maronikolakis, Prof. Dr. Hinrich Schütze and Dr. Axel Wisiorek as part of the ongoing collaborative project AI4Dignity.

Read the full article here

Give us your Feedback

AI@LMU celebrates its sixth month anniversary this month. We always look to improve it. If you have any suggestions or have noticed something amiss, please send us your valuable feedback. Thank you!

UPCOMING EVENTS

Female Summer School on Mathematical Philosophy 2022

This year’s Summer School on Mathematical Philosophy for Female Students at the Munich Center for Mathematical Philosophy (MCMP) will be held online from 01.08. to 05.08. with talks on the philosophy of AI. The topics for the lecture streams this year are "Explanations in mathematical and computational sciences" by Prof. Atoosa Kasirzadeh, Ph.D. from the University of Edinburgh and "Idealizations in machine Learning" by Prof. Dr. Emily Sullivan from Eindhoven University of Technology

Read more here

What is AI in Education and How can it be Harnessed in Service of Front-line Education?

As part of the lecture series International Munich Lectures in Teacher Education Research Prof. Dr. Kaśka Porayska-Pomsta from University College London will give a guest lecture on AI as a tool for supporting learning and teaching along with ethical considerations. The talk will be held online at 6:00 pm on 30.07.

Read more here

AIM@LMU Ringvorlesung

The AIM@LMU Ringvorlesung by the Chair of Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning will feature four speakers in July: Prof. Dr. Stefan Feuerriegel on "Leveraging AI to reach the Sustainable Development Goals" (06.07.), Prof. Dr. Sahana Udupa about "AI and Extreme Speech Online" (13.07.), Prof. Dr. Michael Ingrisch on "AI in Radiology" (20.07.), and Prof. Dr. Ines Helm on "AI and the Labor Market" (27.07.)

Read more here
